  "prompt": "What are some of the most famous antifederalist leaders? What did they accomplish?",
  "response": "Some of the most famous Antifederalist leaders include:\n\n1. Patrick Henry (Virginia)\n- Strongly opposed the Constitution's ratification\n- Famous for his \"Give me liberty or give me death\" speech\n- Argued that the Constitution would create a powerful central government that could threaten individual liberties\n\n2. George Mason (Virginia)\n- Refused to sign the Constitution\n- Authored the Virginia Declaration of Rights\n- Advocated for a Bill of Rights to protect individual liberties\n- His criticisms significantly influenced the eventual addition of the Bill of Rights\n\n3. Samuel Adams (Massachusetts)\n- Opposed the Constitution's centralization of power\n- Argued for stronger state sovereignty\n- Advocated for protecting individual rights\n- His criticism helped push for the Bill of Rights\n\n4. Richard Henry Lee (Virginia)\n- Proposed the initial resolution for independence from Britain\n- Argued against the Constitution's potential for creating a monarchy-like central government\n- Argued for stronger state powers\n\n5. James Lincoln (South Carolina)\n- Vocal opponent of the Constitution\n- Argued that the document would harm smaller states and individual freedoms\n\nTheir primary accomplishments included forcing debates about individual rights, compelling the Federalists to add the Bill of Rights, and ensuring greater protections for state and individual liberties in the final Constitutional framework.",
